definitions.definition: To build or settle into a nest.

examples: We loved the new house and were nesting there in two days!

definitions.definition: To successively neatly fit inside another.
examples: I bought a set of nesting mixing bowls for my mother.

definitions.definition: To place in, or as if in, a nest.
To place one thing neatly inside another, and both inside yet another (and so on).
examples: There would be much more room in the attic if you had nested all the empty boxes.

definitions.definition: To hunt for birds' nests or their contents (usually "go nesting").

main_definition: ( intransitive , of animals ) To build or settle into a nest.
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To settle into a home.
( intransitive ) To successively neatly fit inside another.
( transitive ) To place in, or as if in, a nest.
( transitive ) To place one thing neatly inside another, and both inside yet another (and so on).
( intransitive ) To hunt for birds' nests or their contents (usually "go nesting").
